<paragraph id="71D7160ECDBE16366B4E2626A17937AA" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
A range-restricted subspecies, endemic to NE Greece, Bulgaria and North Macedonia (
<bibRefCitation id="48430D3511329F5B06F90F750751EE06" author="Dimopoulos, P." journalOrPublisher="Botanischer Garten und Botanisches Museum Berlin-Dahlem, Berlin; Hellenic Botanical Society, Athens" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668013" refString="Dimopoulos, P., Raus, T., Bergmeier, E., Constantinidis, T., Iatrou, G., Kokkini, S., Strid, A., D.Tzanoudakis, , 2013. Vascular plants of Greece: An annotated checklist. Botanischer Garten und Botanisches Museum Berlin-Dahlem, Berlin; Hellenic Botanical Society, Athens" title="Vascular plants of Greece: An annotated checklist" year="2013">Dimopoulos et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="C1C55EBA0631837D65A3927FC53A2217" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Cerastium" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cerastium decalvans" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="decalvans">
<emphasis id="CB32543185B887F5F4AE152D9F3FE779" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Cerastium decalvans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been reported from the mountains of Belles, Orvilos, Menikio, Pangeo, Falakro and Lekani in the floristic region of NE Greece (
<bibRefCitation id="F0A216BDA3D71F02423E1F529D95187A" author="Strid, A." journalOrPublisher="Cambridge University Press, Cambridge" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7669378" refString="Strid, A., 1986. Mountain flora of Greece 1. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge" title="Mountain flora of Greece 1" year="1986">Strid 1986</bibRefCitation>
); however, the only records of subsp. 
<taxonomicName id="577CEFFDF89F4F4243B6937DBD8B322C" authority="orbelicum" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Cerastium" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cerastium orbelicum subsp. orbelicum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="orbelicum" subSpecies="orbelicum">Cerastium orbelicum orbelicum</taxonomicName>
come from Mt. Belles and Mt. Menikio (
<bibRefCitation id="D2A05AE72C542250BC3F2AFF6DF1209B" author="Strid, A." journalOrPublisher="Koeltz Scientific Books, Koenigstein" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7669386" refString="Strid, A., 1997. Flora Hellenica 1. Koeltz Scientific Books, Koenigstein" title="Flora Hellenica 1" year="1997">Strid 1997a</bibRefCitation>
). The locality on Mt. Achladovouno is the easternmost border limit of the 
<normalizedToken id="27EEC71DA843FAD21D7648BB12D9CF77" originalValue="subspecies’">subspecies'</normalizedToken>
distribution in Greece.
</paragraph>
